        <p><strong>Where Junia wins:</strong> raw speed and the absolute lowest price for serious bulk generation. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if you want articles that actually rank without the Helpful Content risk. Pick by the job, not the brand.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Junia AI?</h2>
        <p>Junia AI is a budget AI writing platform built for bulk article generation, autoblogging, and SEO-focused content production. It launched in 2023 as a low-cost alternative to Jasper, Writesonic, and Surfer SEO — positioning itself squarely at solo creators, affiliate marketers, and programmatic SEO builders.</p>

        <p>The core suite does five things:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Long-form editor</strong> — Google Docs-style canvas with AI commands</li>
          <li><strong>Bulk article generator</strong> — queue 100+ keywords, generate full articles</li>
          <li><strong>SEO optimization</strong> — built-in keyword scoring (lighter than Surfer)</li>
          <li><strong>WordPress + Shopify auto-publish</strong> — articles push directly to your CMS</li>
          <li><strong>Autoblogging schedules</strong> — set a topic + frequency, articles publish on cron</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Junia is <em>not</em>: a brand voice platform, an enterprise tool, or a managed service. It's an engine. Editorial quality is on you.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Junia is a small bootstrapped team (likely under 15 people) operating remotely. No public funding round. Pricing is intentionally aggressive to grab the SMB and solo creator market that Jasper has vacated post-pivot to enterprise. Customer support is responsive but limited compared to enterprise vendors.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Junia AI features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is focused on volume and price. Here's what actually matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. Long-form editor</h3>
        <p>Standard AI writing canvas. Cmd+J for AI commands, inline rewrites, paragraph generation. Output quality is comparable to Jasper Creator at 1/4 the price — for raw text, you genuinely don't lose much going from Jasper to Junia.</p>

        <h3>2. Bulk article generator (Pro Max + Agency)</h3>
        <p>The headline feature. Paste 100+ keywords into a queue. Junia generates full articles for each — headlines, intros, sections, conclusions. Useful for affiliate site builders covering long-tail keywords. <strong>Critical caveat:</strong> the output requires human review before publishing. Bulk-generated content pushed straight to WordPress is high-risk under Google's 2024 Helpful Content updates.</p>

        <h3>3. SEO optimization</h3>
        <p>Built-in keyword scoring. Junia analyzes SERP results for your target keyword and suggests headings, related terms, and word count. Less granular than Surfer SEO (0.28 ranking correlation) but sufficient for solo workflows.</p>

        <h3>4. WordPress + Shopify integrations</h3>
        <p>Native plugins push generated articles directly into your CMS. WordPress integration is mature — schedule, categorize, tag, attach featured images. Shopify integration covers product descriptions and blog posts.</p>

        <h3>5. Autoblogging schedules</h3>
        <p>The most dangerous feature in the product. Set a topic, pick a frequency (daily, weekly, monthly), and articles publish on schedule with zero human touch. Genuinely impressive technology. Genuinely terrible for long-term SEO unless paired with active editorial review.</p>

